# Cursor Rules — MHG client-spec
# Synced with constitution v3.9.0 (2026-03-11)

## Project Overview

This repository is the central orchestration point for the Mental Health Global
platform. It contains specifications, plans, and task breakdowns — NOT application
code. Implementation happens in the target repositories.

## Spec-First Rule

NEVER write or suggest implementation code directly. All feature work MUST start
with a specification in `specs/NNN-feature-name/`. Use the speckit commands:

1. `/speckit.specify` — create spec
2. `/speckit.plan` — create plan
3. `/speckit.tasks` — generate tasks
4. `/speckit.implement` — execute tasks

## Environments

Do NOT use direct Cloud Run (`*.run.app`) or GCS bucket URLs. Always use:

| Environment | Chat Frontend | Workbench Frontend | Backend API |
|-------------|---------------|--------------------|-------------|
| Dev | https://dev.mentalhelp.chat | https://workbench.dev.mentalhelp.chat | https://api.dev.mentalhelp.chat |
| Prod | https://mentalhelp.chat | https://workbench.mentalhelp.chat | https://api.mentalhelp.chat |

## Target Repositories

| Repository | Role |
|------------|------|
| `chat-backend` | Express.js backend API |
| `chat-frontend` | React frontend (chat) |
| `workbench-frontend` | React frontend (workbench) |
| `chat-frontend-common` | Shared frontend library |
| `chat-ui` | Playwright E2E tests |
| `chat-ci` | Reusable GitHub Actions workflows |
| `chat-infra` | GCP infrastructure |
| `chat-types` | Shared TypeScript types |
| `chat-client` | LEGACY — no new work here |

## Branch Policy

- Feature branches: `NNN-feature-name` (auto-numbered)
- Integration branch: `develop` (never commit directly)
- `main` is promotion-only — via `release/*` branch PR only
- After merge: delete remote branch, delete local branch, sync `develop`

## Feature Workflow (CRITICAL — single branch, single PR per repo)

- **One feature = one `NNN-feature-name` branch per repo**, held open
  until the feature is FULLY implemented + dev-validated end-to-end.
- Iterate inside that branch: commit fixes, push, deploy the branch
  to dev via `gh workflow run deploy.yml --ref <branch> -f environment=dev`,
  re-test — as many times as needed.
- Only ONE PR per repo lands in `develop` per feature. Open it AFTER
  the full feature is validated on dev, NOT after each intermediate
  change.
- NEVER stack multiple PRs for the same feature against `develop`.
  NEVER ask the owner to approve incomplete slices.
- EXCEPTION: a shared library publish (e.g. `chat-types`, `chat-frontend-common`)
  that other repos depend on MAY merge as a prerequisite — but only
  when the dependency boundary is real, not when the change could
  have lived in the consumer's feature branch.
- Production deployment is explicitly out of scope unless the owner
  asks for it. All validation happens on `dev` exclusively.

## Production Deployment Gate (CRITICAL)

**NEVER** create a release branch, open a release PR to `main`, or merge to `main`
without **explicit written approval** from the repository owner. Merging to `main`
triggers automatic production deployment. "Feature is ready" is NOT authorization.

All validation MUST happen on `dev` environment only unless owner instructs otherwise.

## CI Gate (CRITICAL)

**NEVER** merge any PR when CI checks have not run and passed. A PR showing 0 CI
statuses MUST be investigated before merge — the workflow may not have triggered.
CI bypass requires explicit written owner approval documented in the PR.

## Key Files

- Constitution: `.specify/memory/constitution.md`
- Templates: `.specify/templates/`
- Specs: `specs/NNN-feature-name/`
- Commands: `.claude/commands/speckit.*.md`

## Jira Integration

- Jira project: `MTB` at `https://mentalhelpglobal.atlassian.net`
- Each feature → Jira Epic; stories → Stories; tasks → Tasks
- Use `/speckit.sync push` to transition completed tasks to Done in Jira (explicit, not automatic)
- Use `/speckit.sync pull` to update `tasks.md` checkboxes from Jira Done status
- Use `/speckit.sync audit` for a read-only discrepancy report

## Documentation

All docs go to Confluence (https://mentalhelpglobal.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/UD).
Screenshots captured via Playwright MCP against dev environment URLs (above).
